name: Matchmaker
description: Enables the use of an external match-making service in conjunction with PlayFab hosted Game Server instances

properties.name: AuthorizationTicket
properties.description: Session Ticket provided by the client.

properties.name: Authorized
properties.description: Boolean indicating if the user has been authorized to use the external match-making service.

properties.name: PlayFabId
properties.description: PlayFab unique identifier of the account that has been authorized.

properties.name: LobbyId
properties.description: Unique identifier for the Game Server Instance that is being deregistered.

ItemInstance.name: ItemInstance
ItemInstance.description: A unique instance of an item in a user's inventory. Note, to retrieve additional information for an item instance (such as Tags, Description, or Custom Data that are set on the root catalog item), a call to GetCatalogItems is required. The Item ID of the instance can then be matched to a catalog entry, which contains the additional information. Also note that Custom Data is only set here from a call to UpdateUserInventoryItemCustomData.

properties.name: ItemId
properties.description: Unique identifier for the inventory item, as defined in the catalog.

properties.name: ItemInstanceId
properties.description: Unique item identifier for this specific instance of the item.

properties.name: ItemClass
properties.description: Class name for the inventory item, as defined in the catalog.

properties.name: PurchaseDate
properties.description: Timestamp for when this instance was purchased.

properties.name: Expiration
properties.description: Timestamp for when this instance will expire.

properties.name: RemainingUses
properties.description: Total number of remaining uses, if this is a consumable item.

properties.name: UsesIncrementedBy
properties.description: The number of uses that were added or removed to this item in this call.

properties.name: Annotation
properties.description: Game specific comment associated with this instance when it was added to the user inventory.

properties.name: CatalogVersion
properties.description: Catalog version for the inventory item, when this instance was created.

properties.name: BundleParent
properties.description: Unique identifier for the parent inventory item, as defined in the catalog, for object which were added from a bundle or container.

properties.name: DisplayName
properties.description: CatalogItem.DisplayName at the time this item was purchased.

properties.name: UnitCurrency
properties.description: Currency type for the cost of the catalog item.

properties.name: UnitPrice
properties.description: Cost of the catalog item in the given currency.

properties.name: BundleContents
properties.description: Array of unique items that were awarded when this catalog item was purchased.

properties.name: CustomData
properties.description: A set of custom key-value pairs on the inventory item.

properties.name: LobbyId
properties.description: Unique identifier of the Game Server Instance the user is joining.

properties.name: PlayFabId
properties.description: PlayFab unique identifier for the user joining.

properties.name: LobbyId
properties.description: Unique identifier of the Game Server Instance the user is leaving.

properties.name: PlayFabId
properties.description: PlayFab unique identifier for the user leaving.

properties.name: ServerHost
properties.description: IP address of the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: ServerPort
properties.description: Port number for communication with the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: Build
properties.description: Unique identifier of the build running on the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: Region
properties.description: Unique identifier of the build running on the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: GameMode
properties.description: Unique identifier of the build running on the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: Tags
properties.description: Tags for the Game Server Instance

properties.name: LobbyId
properties.description: Unique identifier generated for the Game Server Instance that is registered.

properties.name: Build
properties.description: Unique identifier of the previously uploaded build executable which is to be started.

properties.name: Region
properties.description: Region with which to associate the server, for filtering.

properties.name: GameMode
properties.description: Game mode for this Game Server Instance.

properties.name: CustomCommandLineData
properties.description: Custom command line argument when starting game server process.

properties.name: ExternalMatchmakerEventEndpoint
properties.description: HTTP endpoint URL for receiving game status events, if using an external matchmaker. When the game ends, PlayFab will make a POST request to this URL with the X-SecretKey header set to the value of the game's secret and an application/json body of { "EventName": "game_ended", "GameID": "<gameid>" }.

properties.name: GameID
properties.description: Unique identifier for the game/lobby in the new Game Server Instance.

properties.name: ServerHostname
properties.description: IP address of the new Game Server Instance.

properties.name: ServerPort
properties.description: Port number for communication with the Game Server Instance.

properties.name: PlayFabId
properties.description: PlayFab unique identifier of the user whose information is being requested.

properties.name: MinCatalogVersion
properties.description: Minimum catalog version for which data is requested (filters the results to only contain inventory items which have a catalog version of this or higher).

properties.name: PlayFabId
properties.description: PlayFab unique identifier of the user whose information was requested.

properties.name: Username
properties.description: PlayFab unique user name.

properties.name: TitleDisplayName
properties.description: Title specific display name, if set.

properties.name: Inventory
properties.description: Array of inventory items in the user's current inventory.

properties.name: VirtualCurrency
properties.description: Array of virtual currency balance(s) belonging to the user.

properties.name: VirtualCurrencyRechargeTimes
properties.description: Array of remaining times and timestamps for virtual currencies.

properties.name: IsDeveloper
properties.description: Boolean indicating whether the user is a developer.

properties.name: SteamId
properties.description: Steam unique identifier, if the user has an associated Steam account.

properties.name: SecondsToRecharge
properties.description: Time remaining (in seconds) before the next recharge increment of the virtual currency.

properties.name: RechargeTime
properties.description: Server timestamp in UTC indicating the next time the virtual currency will be incremented.

properties.name: RechargeMax
properties.description: Maximum value to which the regenerating currency will automatically increment. Note that it can exceed this value through use of the AddUserVirtualCurrency API call. However, it will not regenerate automatically until it has fallen below this value.

calls.name: AuthUser
calls.summary: Validates a user with the PlayFab service
calls.requestDetails: This API allows the external match-making service to confirm that the user has a valid Session Ticket for the title, in order to securely enable match-making. The client passes the user's Session Ticket to the external match-making service, which then passes the Session Ticket in as the AuthorizationTicket in this call.

calls.name: DeregisterGame
calls.summary: Inform the matchmaker that a Game Server Instance is removed.

calls.name: PlayerJoined
calls.summary: Informs the PlayFab game server hosting service that the indicated user has joined the Game Server Instance specified

calls.name: PlayerLeft
calls.summary: Informs the PlayFab game server hosting service that the indicated user has left the Game Server Instance specified

calls.name: RegisterGame
calls.summary: Inform the matchmaker that a new Game Server Instance is added.

calls.name: StartGame
calls.summary: Instructs the PlayFab game server hosting service to instantiate a new Game Server Instance

calls.name: UserInfo
calls.summary: Retrieves the relevant details for a specified user, which the external match-making service can then use to compute effective matches
